+GIT: Global Interaction tool
+
+Git is an source code management tool where we store all important files, directories, images, logos etc which uses distributed version control system(VCS) mechanism which provides proper tracking and also benefit of storage cost optimization.
+
V9. git rm: git rm is used for deleting the file from git control.
   command: git rm file/directory
            git commit -m "Deleted the file/directory"


[root@ip-172-31-8-220 devops-repo]# git rm file.txt
rm 'file.txt'
[root@ip-172-31-8-220 devops-repo]# git status
On branch master
Changes to be committed:
  (use "git restore --staged <file>..." to unstage)
        deleted:    file.txt

[root@ip-172-31-8-220 devops-repo]#

[root@ip-172-31-8-220 devops-repo]# git commit -m "Deleted the file.txt"
[master 3874bb4] Deleted the file.txt
 1 file changed, 5 deletions(-)
 delete mode 100644 file.txt
[root@ip-172-31-8-220 devops-repo]#

